#ROOMS
#2400
The Throne Room~
The only thing you can do when you enter is stare.  Large arches
reach well over 100 feet in the air to support the ceiling.  The
entire room is made with the purest white marble.  The floor has been
polished to such a shine that it might as well be a mirror, as have
the walls, and the many pillars helping support the ceiling.  As you
look up to the ceiling, you almost get the impression that there
actually isnt a ceiling, that it just raises up forever, to the
heavens, where the glow that lights the room must be coming from.  As
you return your gaze to a more earthly level, you notice the red
carpet running in front of you.  It is a good 6 feet wide, and runs
to the middle of the room.  In the middle of the room is a raised
dais.  The carpet runs right up to it, and up the steps, where it
stops.  Atop the dais is a large, wooden throne, ornately carved and
beautiful, but not to the point of being obscene.  It looks as if it
is dwarven work, for though it looks to be made of wood at first
glance, upon closer inspection, it is truly stone.  The man wh osits
on it, sits it well, in no more than a deep, forest green cloak and
brown breeches, with a white tunic.  His crown is a circlet of leaves
upon his head.  You wouldnt think him a king, but he is.  As you come
forward, he smiles to you, putting at ease any fears or misgivings in
your heart.  
~
