#2401
The Entryway to the Court~
You are in entryway to the court of Gondor.  To the north stand
two massive white marble doors, closed at the moment.  They are so
well crafted and fashioned that there are no cracks whatsoever in the
doorway.  You follow the door up and up, and notice that it does
finally come to a top at about 75 feet in the air.  As you approach
it, the doors swing open of their own accord and a pure white
radiance floods you through the open doorway.  You notice there are
two lightly armored figures in alcoves to either side of the door,
presumably as door wardens.  The floor of the room you are in is
carpeted in a soft, deep green, providing an interesting counterpoint
to the marbled whiteness of the walls and ceiling.  As you stand
there, you notice to the west is a small side passageway, but only
members of Gondor are allowed in there.  And to the south is a
portcullis leading to a forested courtyard.  
~
