#2404
The Armory~
This place can be described as nothing other than a shrine to
combat.  Racks of weapons and armor line the walls.  Mostly
longswords and long bows, but there is the occassional mace, or axe,
or polearm, a weapon for everyone.  The are many chests lining the
floors, full of spare pieces of equipment that are unneeded by some
members, but that could prove useful to other members.  An old,
scarred soldier sits on a stool in a corner, watching to ensure that
only members of Gondor come in here to make use of the stores.  As
you walk by he looks at you with his one good eye and grins, showing
off his three remaining teeth.  While you browse around the gathered
'toys' he tells you many stories of his youth, when he traveled
around with the great armies, and fought under kings almost as great
as Imrahil.  
~
