#2406
Before the Gate to the Castle~
The gate before you is one of the largest you have ever seen. 
While not quite as massive as the one to the city proper in the outer
wall, it's still a monstrosity unto itself.  Easily 30 feet tall,
with slits in the guard tower atop it, perfect for archers.  The
portcullis is currently up, and the doors open, but from the look of
things, you wouldn't want to be on the wrong side of it.  But while
impressive, the castle is not necessarily imposing.  It has been
built in such a way that it seems an almost natural part of the
landscape.  On the other side of the gate, you see a large courtyard,
also a convenient bailey, and in the middle of that, the keep itself.
~
