#2445
Gondor's Meeting Room~
As you ascend up the stairs, and come up into the meeting room,
you are first dazzled by the brilliant sunlight streaming in through
the four windows, one facing each of the cardinal directions.  Only,
It's not really fair to call them just windows.  There are balconies
outside of each, with green and growing plants, flowers, and other
greenery, softening the room pleasantly.  A breeze comes in through
the northern window, bringing with it the smell of the roses in that
direction with it.  In the middle of the large room isa perfectly
round table.  Surrounding it are wooden chairs, with comfortable
padding placed in them to ease the discomfort of sitting through a
long meeting.  A brazier burns in the middle of the table, with
incense in it, further providing for comfort.  A staff of servants
stands ready with cold drinks to soothe parched throats from lengthy
speeches or proposals.  You take another look at the table, however,
and you notice it is made of black marble, very beautifully crafted,
and carved with elvish runes around the outer edge.  It is shined to
a glassy sheen, and you can see your face reflected clearly on it.  
~
